- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a framework for analyzing social networks of historical figures. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also a likely category as the paper deals with social research topics. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes a novel group partition algorithm. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper uses the China Biographical Database Project (CBDB) dataset. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also relevant as the paper discusses the use of digital humanities in social research.
